        "id": "35ef859ec1a87d57",
        "text": "<ul><li><b>Trusted.</b> Trust management mechanisms should be a core element in the new patterns so that developers can use patterns validated by actors (individuals, organizations...) they trust, with guarantees of authenticity, integrity and with reliable assessment of their quality and reputation. Therefore, we propose the inclusion of mechanisms guaranteeing the quality and integrity of the pattern. This is related to the concept of provenance in the sense that it covers origin and authorship, but also the aspects of reuse, adaptation and extension, also inherent to provenance. Of course, relations between patterns must be considered. Additionally, we believe it would be useful to have mechanisms for associating some sort of “reputation” (i.e. community-based evaluation) to the patterns, but this should be done independently to the pattern content. In this context, the concept of \"Endorsement\" can be a valid solution as it allows trust to be based on actors other than the pattern creator.</li>\n</ul>"
